    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Chop your<strong> potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 18 min</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/harissa-cod-and-cherry-tomato-traybake/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Pat your <strong>fish fillet[s]</strong> dry with<strong> </strong>kitchen paper</p><p>Add <strong>half</strong> your<strong> ground smoked paprika</strong> (save the rest for later!) to a plate with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong> and mix it together</p><p>Add the <strong>fish fillet[s]</strong> to the plate and turn until fully coated, then set aside \u2013 this is your <strong>smoky</strong> <strong>fish fillet</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/harissa-cod-and-cherry-tomato-traybake/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your<strong> cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/harissa-cod-and-cherry-tomato-traybake/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Trim, then chop your <strong>green beans </strong>in half</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/harissa-cod-and-cherry-tomato-traybake/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>After the initial 18 min, remove the tray[s] from the oven</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong> and <strong>chopped green beans</strong> to the tray[s] with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Sprinkle over the <strong>remaining ground smoked paprika </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/harissa-cod-and-cherry-tomato-traybake/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>smoky fish fillet[s] </strong>to the tray[s] with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for a further 12-15 min or until the fish is cooked through, the potatoes are crisp and the vegetables have softened \u2013 this is your <strong>smoky fish tray bake</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/harissa-cod-and-cherry-tomato-traybake/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine your <strong>mayo </strong>and<strong> harissa paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) in a small bowl and mix it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>harissa mayo</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/harissa-cod-and-cherry-tomato-traybake/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>smoky fish tray bake</strong> with the<strong> harissa mayo</strong> drizzled over the top</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
